-- Russian Sappers Defuse Bomb Near Theater in Grozny, RIA Novosti Reports
-- B y   P a u l   A b e l s k y
-- 2010-10-26T05:12:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/russian-sappers-defuse-bomb-near-theater-in-grozny-ria-novosti-reports.html
Russian sappers defused a bomb near
a theater in the Chechen capital of Grozny, RIA Novosti
reported, citing unidentified law enforcement officials.  The explosive was found inside a metal container about 70
meters from the entrance to the state theater and concert hall,
the state-run news service reported today.  The bomb, made of 6 kilograms of TNT, was designed to be
detonated via a Nokia mobile phone, RIA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Abelsky in Moscow at 
 pabelsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
